<section class="page__section pt-0 pb-0"><div id="section-get-started" class="toc-item-anchor"></div><h2 title="Get started" class="h--medium section__heading toc-item tablet-45" data-anchor-id="section-get-started">Enable cuML Acceleration of scikit-learn, UMAP, and HDBSCAN With Zero Code Changes</h2>
<p id="ihcigx" class="p--large">Once cuML is installed,  you can access and enable the cuml.accel module to accelerate scikit-learn, UMAP, and HDBSCAN workflows with no code changes. Note that not all cuML estimators are supported in cuml.accel (open beta) today. Read about the <a href="https://docs.rapids.ai/api/cuml/stable/zero-code-change-limitations/" id="iylk2c">known limitations</a> to understand what is and what is not covered.<br><br>To use cuml.accel, enable it using one of these methods before importing scikit-learn, UMAP, or HDBSCAN:<br></p>
<div class="separator separator--60"></div>
<div class="row cards__list">
<div class="col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-lg-6 col-xl-6">
